<html>
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=windows-1252">
    <title>Diabetic Lower limb CASE SHEET</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-size: 8pt;
        line-height: 1.4;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1cm;
        font-family: 'Times New Roman', times, serif;
      }
      
      /* Lists */
      ol, ul {
        margin-left: 10%;
        padding-left: 0;
      }
      
      ul {
        list-style-type: lower-alpha;
      }
      
      ol {
        list-style-type: decimal;
      }
      
      .section {
        margin-bottom: 15px;
      }
      
      h3 {
        font-size: 9pt;
        font-weight: bold;
        margin-top: 15px;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
        color: #333;
        font-family: 'Times New Roman', times, serif;
      }
      
      h4 {
        font-size: 8pt;
        font-weight: bold;
        margin-top: 10px;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        color: #444;
        font-family: 'Times New Roman', times, serif;
      }
      
      p {
        margin: 5px 0;
      }
      
      .indent-1 {
        margin-left: 2em;
      }
      
      .indent-2 {
        margin-left: 4em;
      }

      u {
        color: #2100fd;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: bold;
        font-style: normal;
      }

      b {
        color: #fd0054;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: bold;
        font-style: normal;
      }

      em {
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: bold;
        font-style: normal;
        color: #08cca2;
      }

      strong {
        color: #09a8cc;
        font-weight: bold;
        font-style: normal;
        text-decoration: none;
      }
      .video-container {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        aspect-ratio: 2/ 1; /* Width:Height = 1:2 */
      }

      td {
        padding: 5px;
        font-size: 8pt;
      }
      tr {
        padding: 5px;
        font-size: 8pt;
      }
      .video-container iframe {
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
      }

      iframe {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
      }
      .Red {
        color: rgb(0, 214, 203);
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode">ðŸŒ™ Dark Mode</button>  
      <h3>CEREBELLAR EXAMINATION</h3>

      <p class="Red">This is not how you should approach cases - patient doesnt come qith ceebellar ataxia they come with the cheif complaints below!!!</p>
      <br>
  
      <div class="video-container">
        <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ItJc_6eH_w4" title="Cerebellar Examination - PLAB 2 / UKMLA" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen id="cerebellarExamVideo"></iframe>
      </div>
<br>

      <div class="video-container">
        <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/K8Tn-TXvqes" title="Cerebellar Examination - PLAB 2 / UKMLA" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen id="cerebellarExamVideo"></iframe>
      </div>
      <br>
      <p style="text-align:center; font-style:italic;">Video for reference. Click on timestamped links below to jump to specific sections.</p>
  
      <h4>CASE SCENARIO & HISTORY TAKING <a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=26s" class="timestamp">(0:26 - 2:20)</a></h4>
      <ul>
          <li><strong>Patient:</strong> Mrs. Janet Clarke, 65 years old.</li>
          <li><strong>Referral:</strong> From GP due to suspicion of cerebellar ataxia.</li>
          <li><strong>Background:</strong> Diagnosed with Diabetes (well-controlled).</li>
          <li><strong>Symptoms (Onset 3 months, Worsening):</strong>
              <ul>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=61s" class="timestamp">Clumsiness (1:01)</a>: Difficulty with fine motor skills like knitting.</li>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=87s" class="timestamp">Walking difficulty (1:27)</a>: Feels like she's going to fall, but hasn't fallen.</li>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=104s" class="timestamp">Difficulty holding objects (1:44)</a>: Things slip from her hands.</li>
              </ul>
          </li>
          <li><strong>Differential Diagnosis Questions (Red Flags/Other Causes):</strong>
              <ul>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=143s" class="timestamp">Infection (Fever, UTI signs) (2:23)</a></li>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=150s" class="timestamp">Eye/Ear problems (2:30)</a></li>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=153s" class="timestamp">Control of Diabetes/Hypertension (2:33)</a></li>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=159s" class="timestamp">Stroke/TIA symptoms (weakness, speech issues) (2:39)</a></li>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=170s" class="timestamp">Alcohol History (2:50)</a></li>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=171s" class="timestamp">Family History (2:51)</a></li>
              </ul>
          </li>
      </ul>
  
      <h4>EXAMINATION COMPONENTS <a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=137s" class="timestamp">(Overview starts at 2:17, elements detailed from 3:18)</a></h4>
      <p class="notes">The video references a slide showing these components, and the speaker discusses them generally rather than demonstrating each one sequentially on a patient for the full duration. Specific phrases/tests mentioned are timestamped below.</p>
  
      <h5>SPEECH <a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=142s" class="timestamp">(Discussed at 2:22 and from 3:23)</a></h5>
      <ul>
          <li>Ask patient to repeat phrases:
              <ul>
                  <li>"British Constitution"</li>
                  <li>"Baby Hippopotamus"</li>
                  <li>"42 West Register Street"</li>
              </ul>
          </li>
          <li class="notes">Look for: Dysarthria (slurred speech), scanning speech (syllables separated), staccato speech (jerky, explosive).</li>
      </ul>
  
      <h5>EYE MOVEMENTS (Nystagmus) <a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=150s" class="timestamp">(Discussed at 2:30 and from 3:31)</a></h5>
      <ul>
          <li>Ask patient to follow your finger in an "H" pattern.</li>
          <li>Observe for nystagmus (involuntary rhythmic eye movements).</li>
          <li class="notes">Note direction of fast phase, gaze-evoked nystagmus. Cerebellar nystagmus is typically worse on looking towards the side of the lesion.</li>
      </ul>
  
      <h5>CO-ORDINATION</h5>
      <ul>
          <li><strong>Upper Limb:</strong>
              <ul>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=154s" class="timestamp">Finger-to-Nose Test (2:34 and from 3:34)</a>: Patient touches their nose, then your finger, repeatedly. Move your finger to different positions.
                      <br><span class="notes">Look for: Dysmetria (misjudging distance/target), intention tremor (tremor worsens on approaching target), past-pointing.</span>
                  </li>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=155s" class="timestamp">Dysdiadochokinesia (Rapid Alternating Movements) (2:35 and from 3:35)</a>: E.g., rapidly pronating and supinating hands on thighs or in the air.
                      <br><span class="notes">Look for: Clumsy, irregular, slow movements.</span>
                  </li>
              </ul>
          </li>
          <li><strong>Lower Limb:</strong>
              <ul>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=156s" class="timestamp">Heel-to-Shin Test (2:36 and from 3:36)</a>: Patient places one heel on the opposite knee and slides it down the shin to the ankle.
                      <br><span class="notes">Look for: Inaccuracy, wobbling, decomposition of movement.</span>
                  </li>
              </ul>
          </li>
      </ul>
  
      <h5>BALANCE (Gait & Stance)</h5>
      <ul>
          <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=159s" class="timestamp">Gait (Walking) (2:39 and from 3:39)</a>: Observe patient walking normally.
              <br><span class="notes">Look for: Broad-based gait, unsteadiness, staggering, difficulty turning.</span>
          </li>
          <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=159s" class="timestamp">Tandem Gait (Heel-to-Toe Walking) (2:39 and from 3:39)</a>: Walking in a straight line, placing heel directly in front of the toe of the other foot.
              <br><span class="notes">Exacerbates unsteadiness.</span>
          </li>
          <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=160s" class="timestamp">Romberg Test (2:40 and from 3:40)</a>: Patient stands with feet together, arms by their sides.
              <ol>
                  <li>Eyes open.</li>
                  <li>Eyes closed (stand by to prevent fall).</li>
              </ol>
              <span class="notes">Positive if patient sways significantly or loses balance *only when eyes are closed* (suggests sensory ataxia). If unsteady with eyes open, more likely cerebellar. In cerebellar ataxia, patient is often unsteady with eyes open and closed.</span>
          </li>
      </ul>
  
      <h5>TONE <a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=175s" class_timestamp">(Mentioned as additional at 2:55 and from 3:54)</a></h5>
      <ul>
          <li>Assess muscle tone in upper and lower limbs (passive movements).
          <br><span class="notes">Look for: Hypotonia (decreased tone) can be a feature of cerebellar lesions, especially acute ones. Pendular reflexes may also be seen.</span>
          </li>
      </ul>
  
  
      <h4>MANAGEMENT DISCUSSION <a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=255s" class="timestamp">(Starts around 4:15)</a></h4>
      <ul>
          <li>Keep patient in hospital.</li>
          <li><strong>Investigations:</strong>
              <ul>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=262s" class="timestamp">Blood tests (4:22)</a> (to rule out infection, metabolic causes)</li>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=265s" class="timestamp">Urine test (4:25)</a> (for UTI)</li>
                  <li><a href="https://youtu.be/ItJc_6eH_w4?t=271s" class="timestamp">CT / MRI Scan of the brain (4:31)</a> (to look for structural lesions like tumor, stroke, atrophy)</li>
              </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Explain that symptoms are concerning and further investigation is needed to find the cause.</li>
      </ul>
  
  
      <script>
          document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
              const videoPlayer = document.getElementById('cerebellarExamVideo');
              const timestampLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.timestamp');
              const baseEmbedUrl = 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/ItJc_6eH_w4';
  
              timestampLinks.forEach(link => {
                  link.addEventListener('click', function(event) {
                      event.preventDefault(); 
  
                      const href = this.getAttribute('href');
                      let seconds = null;
  
                      const timeMatchSeconds = href.match(/t=(\d+)s?/);
                      if (timeMatchSeconds && timeMatchSeconds[1]) {
                          seconds = parseInt(timeMatchSeconds[1]);
                      } else {
                          // Fallback for URLs that might use ?start=XX
                          const timeMatchStart = href.match(/[?&]start=(\d+)/);
                          if (timeMatchStart && timeMatchStart[1]) {
                              seconds = parseInt(timeMatchStart[1]);
                          }
                      }
  
                      if (seconds !== null) {
                          videoPlayer.src = `${baseEmbedUrl}?start=${seconds}&autoplay=1&rel=0`;
                      } else {
                          console.warn("Could not parse time from link: " + href);
                          // Optionally, just load the video from the start if parsing fails
                          videoPlayer.src = baseEmbedUrl + '?autoplay=1&rel=0'; 
                      }
                  });
              });
          });
      </script>
  

         <script src="harsha_iframe_youtube_player.js"></script>
      <script src="theme-toggle.js"></script>
  </body>
  </html>
</html>
